<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="25" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="25">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="25">
<bibRefCitation author="Lourenco, WR" journalOrPublisher="Entomologische Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum Hamburg" pageId="30" pageNumber="45" pagination="45 - 52" title="About the presence of the genus Buthus Leach, 1815 in the Arabian Peninsula and description of a new species (Scorpiones, Buthidae)." volume="15" year="2008">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Lourenço">Lourenco</normalizedToken>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
stated that 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. o." pageId="10" pageNumber="25" rank="subspecies" species="o." subspecies="zeylensis">B. o. zeylensis</taxonomicName>
might be a distinct species from 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. berberensis" pageId="10" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="berberensis">B. berberensis</taxonomicName>
, but that further material was required to confirm this possibility. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kovarik, F" journalOrPublisher="Euscorpius" pageId="30" pageNumber="45" pagination="1 - 6" title="Buthusawashensis sp. n. from Ethiopia (Scorpiones: Buthidae)." url="http://www.science.marshall.edu/fet/euscorpius/p2011_128.pdf" volume="128" year="2011">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Kovařík">Kovarik</normalizedToken>
(2011)
</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. o." pageId="10" pageNumber="25" rank="subspecies" species="o." subspecies="zeylensis">B. o. zeylensis</taxonomicName>
a colour morph of 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. berberensis" pageId="10" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="berberensis">B. berberensis</taxonomicName>
present in juveniles and some males.
</paragraph>
